{"title_page": "1963 Tangerine Bowl", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA football yearly game\n| Game Name = Tangerine Bowl\n| Oprional Subheader = \n| Title Sponsor = \n| Image = \n| Caption =\n| Date Game Played = December 28\n| Year Game Played = 1963\n| Football Season = 1963\n| Stadium = [[Tangerine Bowl (stadium)|Tangerine Bowl]]\n| City = [[Orlando, Florida]]\n| Attendance = 7,500<ref name=latimes />\n| MVP = Sharon Miller<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/223888501/?terms=valuable |title=Hilltopper Defense Does Job |first=Bob |last=Bassine |url-access=subscription |newspaper=[[Orlando Sentinel]] |via=newspapers.com |date=December 29, 1963 |accessdate=March 11, 2017}}</ref>\n| Visitor School = Western Kentucky State College\n| Visitor Name Short = Western Kentucky\n| Visitor Nickname = Hilltoppers\n| Visitor Conference = [[Ohio Valley Conference]]\n| Visitor Coach = [[Nick Denes]]\n| Visitor Record = 9\u20130\u20131\n| Visitor1 = 0\n| Visitor2 = 14\n| Visitor3 = 6\n| Visitor4 = 7\n| Home School = Coast Guard Academy\n| Home Name Short = Coast Guard\n| Home Nickname =  Bears\n| Home Conference = Independent\n| Home Coach = [[Otto Graham]]\n| Home Record = 8\u20130\n| Home1 = 0\n| Home2 = 0\n| Home3 = 0\n| Home4 = 0\n| game link = Citrus Bowl\n}}\nThe '''1963 Tangerine Bowl''' was an [[NCAA Division II|NCAA College Division]] game following the 1963 season, between the [[Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football|Western Kentucky Hilltoppers]]<ref>http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/w/western_kentucky/1960-1964_yearly_results.php</ref> and the [[Coast Guard Bears football|Coast Guard Bears]].<ref>http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/active/c/coast_guard/1960-1964_yearly_results.php</ref> Western Kentucky [[quarterback]] Sharon Miller was named the game's most valuable player.<ref name=hartford />\n\n==Notable participants==\n[[1963 Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football team|Western Kentucky]] [[linebacker]] [[Dale Lindsey]] and [[running back]] Jim Burt were selected in the [[1965 NFL Draft]]. Lindsey has subsequently coached at both the college and professional levels, and in December 2012 became the head coach of the [[San Diego Toreros football| San Diego Toreros]].<ref>http://www.usdtoreros.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/dale_lindsey_348466.html</ref> Lindsey, Burt, and head coach [[Nick Denes]] are inductees of the university's athletic hall of fame.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wkusports.com/ot/hall-of-fame-2.html |title=WKU Athletic Hall of Fame |website=wkusports.com |accessdate=March 3, 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102080108/http://www.wkusports.com/ot/hall-of-fame-2.html |archivedate=January 2, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nCoast Guard head coach [[Otto Graham]] is an inductee of both the [[College Football Hall of Fame]] and the [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]].\n\n==Scoring summary==\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=WK|HomeName=CG|state=}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=7:23\n| Team=WK\n| DrivePlays=6\n| DriveLength=32\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=Sharon Miller\n| yards=12\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=Sam Clark\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=5:00\n| Team=WK\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=John Mutchler\n| QB=Sharon Miller\n| yards=20\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=Sam Clark\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=\n| Team=WK\n| DrivePlays=3\n| DriveLength=67\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=Stan Napper\n| QB=Sharon Miller\n| yards=57\n| kickresult=blocked by Roger Roberts\n| Kicker=Sam Clark\n| Visitor=20\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=13:59\n| Team=WK\n| DrivePlays=1\n| DriveLength=14\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=Jim Burt\n| yards=14\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=Sam Clark\n| Visitor=27\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=27|Home=0}}\n<ref name=lati